{{Infobox cycling race report | name = 2000 Vuelta a Venezuela | image = | image_caption = | date = October 17 &ndash; October 23 | series = | stages = 13 | distance = 1874.4 | unit = km | time = 44h 52' 46" | speed = 41.770 | first = [[Álvaro Lozano]] | first_nat = COL | first_team = Colombia National Team | first_color = red | second = [[Yeison Delgado]] | second_nat = VEN | second_team = Triple Gordo Gob. | third = [[Álvaro Sierra]] | third_nat = COL | third_team = Triple Gordo | points = [[Gil Cordovés]] | points_nat = CUB | points_team = Gobernacíon del Zulía | sprints = [[Gil Cordovés]] | sprints_nat = CUB | sprints_team = Gobernacíon del Zulía | mountains = [[Rodolfo Camacho]] | mountains_nat = COL | mountains_team = Triple Gordo | previous = [[1999 Vuelta a Venezuela|1999]] | next = [[2001 Vuelta a Venezuela|2001]] }}
The 37th edition of the annual '''[[Vuelta a Venezuela]]''' was held from October 17 to October 29, 2000. The stage race started in [[San Fernando de Apure|San Fernando]], and ended in [[San Cristóbal, Táchira|San Cristóbal]].
