[[File:TowelTablet.jpg|thumb|photo of towel tablet]]
A '''towel tablet''' is a fiber [[towel]] that is compressed into the shape and size of a small [[Tablet (pharmacy)|tablet]].{{clarify|date=January 2011}} The towel tablet expands when [[water]] is added to the tablet. Typically the expanded towel size is approximately 26&nbsp;cm by 20&nbsp;cm (10" x 8"). Typical uses are for [[travel]], large events, and other situations where [[Disposable towel|disposable hygiene towels]] are needed.

The compressed toilet tablet is made from 100% natural viscose rayon, which is a fiber of regenerated cellulose. It is a β-D-glucose polymer having the [[empirical formula]] (C6H10O5)n.

[[Cellulose fiber|Cellulose]] is structurally similar to cotton and is generally derived from various plants like Soy, Bamboo or Sugarcane.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.blognox.com/compressed-toilet-paper-tablet/|title=Compressed toilet paper tablet {{!}} Revolutionize your camping experience|date=2017-09-15|work=BlogNox|access-date=2018-10-05|language=en-US}}</ref>

